<h2 id="a082736" class="entry-title"><a href="http://blog.makezine.com/archive/2010/12/homemade_plastic_extrusion_system.html">Homemade plastic extrusion system</a></h2>

<p><iframe title="YouTube video player" class="youtube-player" type="text/html" width="600" height="481" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/anqKC0i0a7Y?hl=en&start=0&fs=1&rel=0&showinfo=0&ap=%2526fmt%3D18" frameborder="0"></iframe></p>

<p>MAKE subscriber Rob Torcellini of Eastford, CT, sent in his extrusion system for turning HDPE pellets into thin, textured strips his plants liked.</p>

<blockquote> I built a <a href="http://web4deb.blogspot.com/2010/12/plastic-extruder-for-growing-media.html">plastic extrusion system</a> to make synthetic growing media for my aquaponics system. It uses the Teensy AVR microprocessor from PJRC, an old windshield wiper motor and a few Legos!</blockquote>



<div class="asset-meta">
<p class="nfo">Posted by <a href="http://www.nerdage.net">John Baichtal</a> |
