<h2 id="a082601" class="entry-title"><a href="http://blog.makezine.com/archive/2010/12/diy_body_scanner_1.html">DIY body scanner</a></h2>

<p><object width="600" height="366"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/vDyo_OQFdAc&hl=en&start=0&fs=1&rel=0&showinfo=0&ap=%2526fmt%3D18"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/vDyo_OQFdAc&hl=en&start=0&fs=1&rel=0&showinfo=0&ap=%2526fmt%3D18" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="600" height="366"></embed></object></p>

<p>Extreme maker and all-around bare metal hacker <a href="http://www.jeriellsworth.com/">Jeri Ellsworth</a> cobbled together this <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vDyo_OQFdAc">DIY TSA-like body scanner</a> using a feed horn from a surplus satellite dish, an optical mouse, some components, and copious amounts of hot glue. [via <a href="http://hackaday.com/2010/12/03/make-your-own-tsa-naked-scanner/">hackaday</a>]</p>



