<h2 id="a082575" class="entry-title"><a href="http://blog.makezine.com/archive/2010/12/heat_shrink_fuse_holder.html">Heat shrink fuse holder</a></h2>

<span class="mt-enclosure mt-enclosure-image" style="display: inline;"><img alt="fuseholder1.jpeg" src="http://blog.makezine.com/fuseholder1.jpeg" width="550" height="308" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></span>
<span class="mt-enclosure mt-enclosure-image" style="display: inline;"><img alt="fuseholder2.jpeg" src="http://blog.makezine.com/fuseholder2.jpeg" width="550" height="308" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></span>
<span class="mt-enclosure mt-enclosure-image" style="display: inline;"><img alt="fuseholder3.jpeg" src="http://blog.makezine.com/fuseholder3.jpeg" width="550" height="308" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></span>

<p>I love this clever <a href="http://sleepygeek.org/projects.fuseholder">fuse holder</a> that a reader sent in. All it takes is some heat shrink tubing, a couple of small springs, and wire.</p>



