<h2 id="a082235" class="entry-title"><a href="http://blog.makezine.com/archive/2010/11/macro_lens_hack_for_under_a_dollar.html">Macro lens hack for under a dollar</a></h2>

<span class="mt-enclosure mt-enclosure-image" style="display: inline;"><img alt="50centmacrolens.jpg" src="http://blog.makezine.com/50centmacrolens.jpg" width="600" height="450" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></span>

<p>Does your camera's focal range not have the chops to take quality close-ups? Why make things complicated? Just tape on a lens from a pair of dollar store reading glasses. Sean Lee shared this <a href="http://makeprojects.com/Project/A-Fifty-Cent-Macro-Lens/409/1">hack on Make: Projects</a>, and posted impressive before and after shots, especially for a paltry 50 cents. </p>



<div class="asset-meta">
